RIP Pèle - The Brasilero soccer hero who is truly the GOAT. I was lucky to be present (playing with Herbie Mann) at his final match in October 1977 (Cosmos vs Santos at Giants Stadium) - Years later I met him in line at a pharmacy near NBC Studios (30 Rock) where we taped Late Night with David Letterman. We shook hands and he was as graceful a person as he was a poet on the pitch. After his last game, he made a speech and ended it by having the whole stadium chanting, “LOVE, LOVE, LOVE, LOVE, LOVE…..”! His spirit will live on in so many people around the world, including myself. I’ll never forget his greatness. 💙👊🏽🙇🏼🙏🏼⚽️🇧🇷♥️

Jeff Young RIP. It’s still sinking in, the loss of such a dear brother. I counted on Jeff musically and as a friend. He was an honest, earnest, talented, soulful artist-as-well-as-team player that I was a fan of way before we became friends. Today I'm feeling very grateful for 38 YEARS of sobriety. On March 1, 1985 I checked into rehab at Gracie Hospital in NYC because my life was in shambles. My relationships were falling apart, my professional life was going away, I was sabotaging really great work by not showing up, I was shunning family and those that loved me and knew me and wanted to help. But finally I asked myself "Are you happy?". Things were such a mess I couldn't even lie and say "yes". It was then or never. I got the OK from Laverne Washington at Gracie who found a space for me. I checked in & thanks to all the great people there, which included Susan Brecker, Miguel Contreras, Laverne, fellow addicts that included Mac Rebennack (the others will remain anonymous). Thanks to sober friends in and out of "the rooms", I remain sober today...ODAAT #grateful #thisboyslife

I’m beyond sad to learn of the sudden passing of my dear friend, legendary bassist Michael Rhodes. He was such a fantastic musician. Monumental records by Vince Gill, Kenny Rogers, Rodney Crowell, Steve Winwood, Nancy Griffith, Marty Stuart, Shawn Colvin, Dixie Chicks, Larry Carlton, LeAnn Times, India.Arie, Stevie Nicks, Bob Seger,  Willie Nelson, Joe Bonamassa… his discography goes on and on and on in many genres. Whenever I had sessions to do in Nashville Michael would always deliver a pile of basses for me to choose from so I didn’t have to ship or carry them down from NYC. He was funny, a fellow Beatles freak and a scientist of “tone”. A great friend who I’ll miss terribly. RIP Mike …🙏🏼💙#thisboyslife

I’m sorry to learn of the passing of my friend Ryuichi Sakamoto. He was a great Japanese composer, record producer, and actor who had mastered a diverse range of styles as a solo artist and as a member of Yellow Magic Orchestra. With his bandmates Haruomi Hosono and Yukihiro Takahashi, Sakamoto influenced and pioneered a number of electronic music genres. My thoughts are with his family and YMO bandmate Hosono-san. My condolences especially to Akiko Yano and their daughter Miu. Sending big hugs 🙏💙🙇‍♂️RIP Ryuchi-san #thisboyslife
